title: Robert C. O'Brien
added: In November 2020, O'Brien traveled to the Philippines and sought an extension of the U.S.-Philippines Visiting Forces Agreement, under which the U.S. military is able to cooperate with the Philippines armed forces. On the same trip, O'Brien visited Vietnam to discuss economic and security issues, especially the threat posed by China.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jennings |first1=Ralph |title=High-Level US Visit to Asia Seen as Locking In Trump's Tough China Policy {{!}} Voice of America - English |url=https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/high-level-us-visit-asia-seen-locking-trumps-tough-china-policy |access-date=2 December 2020 |work=www.voanews.com |agency=Voice of America |publisher=Voice of America |date=23 November 2020 |language=en}}</ref>
